  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various methods:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for large cash transactions\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing money movement through multiple jurisdictions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n\n3. Prosecution Strategies\n- Targeting financial intermediaries\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Criminal charges with significant penalties\n\n4. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight\n- Strict compliance requirements for banks\n- Regular audits and inspections\n- Significant fines for non-compliance\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities.",
